{"id":34137,"date":"2020-04-21T13:45:00","date_gmt":"2020-04-21T09:45:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=34137"},"modified":"2020-04-21T13:45:59","modified_gmt":"2020-04-21T09:45:59","slug":"guide-us-to-path-of-islam","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/04\/21\/guide-us-to-path-of-islam\/","title":{"rendered":"Abdullah on Islam: O Allah, guide us to the path of Islam"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Shaqiq reported: Abdullah ibn Mas\u2019ud, may Allah be pleased with him, used to say often in his supplications, \u201cOur Lord, set things right between us and guide us to the path of Islam. Save us from darkness and bring us to the light. Keep obscenities away from us, the outward and inward among them. Bless us in our hearing, our seeing, our hearts, our wives, and our children. Accept our repentance for you are the Relenting, the Merciful. Make us grateful for your bounties, praising you for them and proclaiming them openly, and perfect them for us.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-Adab al-Mufrad 630<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Sahih<\/em><\/strong> (authentic) according to Al-Albani<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u0646 \u0634\u064e\u0642\u0650\u064a\u0642 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0646 \u0645\u0633\u0639\u0648\u062f \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u064a\u064f\u0643\u0652\u062b\u0650\u0631\u064f \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u064a\u064e\u062f\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0647\u064e\u0624\u064f\u0644\u0627\u064e\u0621\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u062f\u0651\u064e\u0639\u064e\u0648\u064e\u0627\u062a\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0628\u0651\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u0644\u0650\u062d\u0652 \u0628\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0646\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0648\u064e\u0627\u0647\u0652\u062f\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0627 \u0633